title: Pork & Ramen Stir-Fry
summary: The recipe Pork & Ramen Stir-Fry is ready in around 30 minutes and is definitely an excellent dairy free option for lovers of Japanese food. This recipe serves 4. For $2.99 per serving, this recipe covers 30% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One portion of this dish contains roughly 33g of protein, 18g of fat, and a total of 460 calories. A couple people made this recipe, and 74 would say it hit the spot. Head to the store and pick up pork loin chops, sugar, garlic cloves, and a few other things to make it today. It works well as a main course. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 89%. This score is awesome. Try Pork & Ramen Stir-Fry, 20 Minute Sweet & Spicy Pork Ramen Stir Fry, and Beef and Cabbage Stir Fry for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are great choices for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 22 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling
productMatches.description:
Despite its still youthful freshness it shows the fine fruity Riesling characteristic and an underlying hint of mineral from the blue/grey Devonian slate soil.

Serve this refreshing wine slightly chilled! As aperitif and, especially when more matured, in combination with seafood or poultry.

instructions: Directions                                                                                In a small bowl, whisk the first five ingredients until blended. In a large skillet, heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium-high heat. Add pork; stir-fry 2-3 minutes or until no longer pink. Remove from pan.                                                                                           In same pan, stir-fry broccoli in remaining oil 3 minutes. Add coleslaw mix, bamboo shoots and garlic; stir-fry 3-4 minutes longer or until broccoli is crisp-tender. Stir in soy sauce mixture and pork; heat through.                                                                                           Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions, discarding or saving seasoning packets for another use. Drain noodles; add to pork mixture and toss to combine.                                        Yield: 4 servings.                                                                                                                         Originally published as Pork & Ramen Stir-Fry in  Simple & DeliciousAugust/September 2013, p29                                                                                                                            Print                                                                                    Add to Recipe Box                            Email a Friend

steps.step: In a small bowl, whisk the first five ingredients until blended. In a large skillet, heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add pork; stir-fry 2-3 minutes or until no longer pink.
In same pan, stir-fry broccoli in remaining oil 3 minutes.
Add coleslaw mix, bamboo shoots and garlic; stir-fry 3-4 minutes longer or until broccoli is crisp-tender. Stir in soy sauce mixture and pork; heat through.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions, discarding or saving seasoning packets for another use.
Drain noodles; add to pork mixture and toss to combine.
